messages.text:
Hello, my dear diary! Today I want to tell you about a book by Dan Brown, The Da Vinci Code.

Why did I decide to read this book? It‚Äôs simple: my friends had read it before and told me about it. They said that Dan Brown had a conflict with the Vatican because he wrote some secret information about Catholicism. Dan Brown claims that all the information is true, but there are no scientific facts in the book.

The author wrote that it is not a historical or scientific book; it is a novel, and the reader independently decides whether it is true or not. But despite this, I think Dan is a master.

When I was reading, I felt elated. The magnificent story starts in Paris. Many details make the story really interesting and easy to read.

This book left me with many questions and optimistic emotions. I recommend reading this book.

Dan Brown claims that all the information is true, but there are no scientific facts in the book.

The author wrote that it is not a historical or scientific book; it is a novel, and the reader independently decides whether it is true or not. But despite this, I think Dan is a master.

When I was reading, I felt elated. The magnificent story starts in Paris. Many details make the story really interesting and easy to read.

This book left me with many questions and optimistic emotions. I recommend reading this book.
